                        <title xml:lang="he">ספר המשיב : סודות על התורה</title>
                        
                        
                        
                        <note>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>The manuscript begins with the end of the commentary on Bereshit and finishes with the pericope Ṿa-yetse.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>There are marginal notes both in Hebrew, Spanish and Latin throughout the manuscript.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Some anti-christian phrases have been omitted by the scribe, see e.g., folio 82v.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>See further <ref target="Scholem_1930" type="page">85-89</ref>; <ref target="Sefunot" type="number">11</ref> (1972), pp. 73 nn; <ref target="Sefunot" type="number">17</ref> (1984), p. 185.</p>
                        
                        
                        
